WEBVTT

00:03.002 --> 00:04.922
[YUTA]
With supplies being limited,

00:04.964 --> 00:07.090
we'll need to add a rule
allowing passage

00:07.132 --> 00:08.592
in and out of the colony.

00:09.551 --> 00:12.137
But I can't afford
to let players like Dhruv,

00:12.179 --> 00:14.556
who attack people
indiscriminately,

00:14.598 --> 00:16.099
leave the barriers.

00:16.600 --> 00:19.186
I should wait until the players
like him are eliminated

00:19.227 --> 00:21.188
from the other colonies first.

00:21.229 --> 00:24.065
Communication between colonies
is a must.

00:24.107 --> 00:26.401
There's the two rules
Fushiguro proposed.

00:26.443 --> 00:27.653
A means of communication,

00:27.695 --> 00:29.613
and passage
in and out of the colonies.

00:29.655 --> 00:31.198
So we'll need
four additional rules

00:31.239 --> 00:33.241
to get the situation
under control.

00:33.534 --> 00:36.411
Everyone's still at their
physical and emotional limit

00:36.453 --> 00:37.621
from Shibuya.

00:38.873 --> 00:40.165
Gojo.

00:40.207 --> 00:43.210
I won't let you kill
your best friend twice.

00:44.336 --> 00:46.881
I'll kill Kenjaku myself.

00:46.922 --> 00:49.758
I'll get the 400 points
on my own.

00:49.800 --> 00:52.845
JUJUTSU KAISEN

00:56.682 --> 00:58.475
Okay, you can all come out now.

00:59.100 --> 01:01.102
I think we should continue
making our way north

01:01.144 --> 01:02.646
to the edge of the barrier.

01:02.688 --> 01:04.023
[GIRL] Can you carry me?

01:04.481 --> 01:06.233
[MOTHER]
Just hang in there, sweetheart.

01:06.274 --> 01:08.151
Why don't we take a quick rest?

01:08.193 --> 01:09.152
We're safe here.

01:09.194 --> 01:10.779
This stadium
was being controlled

01:10.821 --> 01:12.447
by the sorcerer I just defeated.

01:12.489 --> 01:15.784
Any player that comes along
will be pretty hesitant to--

01:15.826 --> 01:17.118
- [rumbling]
- [MAN 1] What's that sound?

01:20.789 --> 01:23.124
[YUTA] Quick.
Get into the stadium.

01:23.166 --> 01:24.167
[MAN 2] Let's go!

01:24.209 --> 01:26.378
- [panicked chatter]
- Hurry up.

01:26.420 --> 01:29.924
[men panting, whimpering]

01:29.965 --> 01:31.216
[man in blue hoodie screams]

01:31.258 --> 01:32.259
[gasps]

01:33.552 --> 01:35.012
Help! Help me!

01:37.180 --> 01:38.139
[grunts]

01:38.181 --> 01:39.516
[♪ intense music playing]

01:40.976 --> 01:43.687
[YUTA] Wait,
are these cockroaches real?

01:44.103 --> 01:45.397
[vomits]

01:45.439 --> 01:46.481
[YUTA] Damn!

01:52.029 --> 01:54.406
- Rika, knock it down!
- [MAN 1] Hurry!

01:55.490 --> 01:56.909
- [RIKA] Okay!
- [girl whimpers]

01:56.951 --> 01:57.993
[MAN 1] Run!

02:00.788 --> 02:02.414
♪

02:10.505 --> 02:13.968
- Kogane, is that a player?
- Yes.

02:14.009 --> 02:16.762
That is a player
called Kurourushi.

02:17.846 --> 02:20.724
[YUTA] So some players
are cursed spirits.

02:21.308 --> 02:24.436
EPISODE 59
SENDAI COLONY

02:27.606 --> 02:29.650
FESTERING LIFE SWORD

02:31.986 --> 02:33.152
[whooshing]

02:34.362 --> 02:35.405
[slashes]

02:35.739 --> 02:36.865
[clangs, thuds]

02:36.907 --> 02:37.950
[grunts]

02:46.541 --> 02:47.542
[grunts]

02:47.876 --> 02:49.003
[YUTA] I'm being watched.

02:49.795 --> 02:52.589
Likely, it's the other
two players with high points.

02:52.965 --> 02:55.216
[KUROURUSHI]
Why do you interfere?

02:55.258 --> 02:57.552
[YUTA]
Kurourushi is a cursed spirit.

02:57.594 --> 03:00.055
[KUROURUSHI] Why do you kill us?

03:00.639 --> 03:02.016
[YUTA] I can exorcise it.

03:02.057 --> 03:03.934
I just have to drive
positive energy

03:03.976 --> 03:07.146
from my reverse cursed technique
into its body.

03:07.771 --> 03:09.731
I can ask you the same question.

03:09.940 --> 03:10.983
But...

03:11.274 --> 03:14.653
[KUROURUSHI] Because
I like the taste of iron!

03:17.990 --> 03:19.574
[YUTA] I don't want
those other two players

03:19.616 --> 03:22.369
to know I can use
reverse cursed technique.

03:22.410 --> 03:25.039
Rika's protecting everyone
in the stadium.

03:25.080 --> 03:27.206
So I have to
exorcise Kurourushi

03:27.248 --> 03:30.377
without using Rika
or my reverse cursed technique.

03:33.421 --> 03:34.464
[clangs]

03:35.298 --> 03:36.383
[KUROURUSHI] Blinding.

03:36.424 --> 03:37.551
Blinding.

03:37.592 --> 03:38.969
Blinding.

03:41.555 --> 03:42.639
[slashes]

03:52.941 --> 03:53.984
[grunts]

04:07.164 --> 04:08.415
[grunts]

04:10.125 --> 04:11.210
[gasps]

04:12.335 --> 04:13.461
[grunts]

04:13.837 --> 04:15.172
[sword clanging]

04:15.839 --> 04:17.758
[Kurourushi growls]

04:17.799 --> 04:19.051
[slashes]

04:21.553 --> 04:22.596
[coughs]

04:24.472 --> 04:26.767
- [mini Kuros squealing]
- [Yuta groans]

04:27.517 --> 04:28.560
[groans]

04:30.229 --> 04:31.521
[breathing laboriously]

04:32.898 --> 04:34.066
[grunts]

04:34.566 --> 04:35.943
[struggling breaths]

04:35.984 --> 04:37.778
[Kurourushi growls]

04:38.695 --> 04:39.696
[Yuta grunts]

04:39.988 --> 04:41.322
- [bites]
- [Kurourushi gasps]

04:42.741 --> 04:44.534
[wind whooshing]

04:45.827 --> 04:47.121
[cracking]

04:51.875 --> 04:54.293
[KOGANE] You have gained
five points for a kill.

04:54.335 --> 04:56.213
[TAKAKO] I see
that you can use...

04:56.880 --> 04:59.091
- ...reverse cursed technique.
- [gasps]

05:04.972 --> 05:06.014
[Yuta grunts]

05:06.473 --> 05:07.557
[YUTA] What was that?

05:07.599 --> 05:09.350
- A strike?
- [Takako grunts]

05:10.602 --> 05:11.728
[grunts]

05:14.481 --> 05:15.899
[glass shatters]

05:19.236 --> 05:20.821
[YUTA] My arm is back to normal.

05:20.862 --> 05:21.989
I feel fine.

05:22.239 --> 05:25.075
Her technique probably
manipulates space.

05:25.117 --> 05:26.743
But I guess
she can't use that space

05:26.785 --> 05:28.245
to crush her opponents.

05:28.287 --> 05:31.372
It seems to create distortions
like a funhouse mirror.

05:31.957 --> 05:34.084
[TAKAKO] You're wondering
about my technique?

05:34.126 --> 05:36.753
It treats the sky as a surface.

05:38.379 --> 05:39.923
Here, let me show you.

05:39.965 --> 05:42.009
[YUTA]
She's revealing her technique.

05:42.592 --> 05:44.761
[TAKAKO]
Hurry up and attack already.

05:45.262 --> 05:46.513
[YUTA] I have to ask.

05:46.554 --> 05:47.931
You're not someone
who's gonna complain

05:47.973 --> 05:49.933
about getting killed, are you?

05:49.975 --> 05:51.143
I mean, I can understand

05:51.226 --> 05:53.728
powerless people
getting desperate for points,

05:53.770 --> 05:55.022
but a strong person like you

05:55.063 --> 05:56.815
can claim points
whenever they want.

05:57.482 --> 06:00.152
So what's your reason
for actively seeking a fight?

06:00.401 --> 06:01.903
[TAKAKO] This little brat.

06:02.154 --> 06:03.362
Seriously?

06:03.738 --> 06:06.658
Are you modern-day sorcerers
that casual about incarnation?

06:06.700 --> 06:08.160
To us from the old school,

06:08.202 --> 06:10.453
this means coming back
from the dead.

06:10.495 --> 06:13.081
People who lived out
their lives without regrets

06:13.123 --> 06:15.667
wouldn't accept
Kenjaku's offer, would they?

06:16.126 --> 06:17.919
He's really pissing me off.

06:17.961 --> 06:19.546
I like to think
of the Culling Game

06:19.587 --> 06:22.632
as the first step toward
a chance at a second life.

06:22.674 --> 06:25.844
Keep in mind that Kenjaku
set the stage for this.

06:25.886 --> 06:27.428
Anything could happen.

06:27.470 --> 06:29.973
We need to earn points
to prepare ourselves.

06:30.015 --> 06:33.185
I wonder if someone like you
has any friends or lovers.

06:35.020 --> 06:36.063
Huh?

06:36.688 --> 06:37.898
You know what?

06:38.023 --> 06:40.150
Until recently, I didn't
have any friends either.

06:40.192 --> 06:41.651
Not that I feel sorry for you.

06:42.069 --> 06:43.737
[TAKAKO] Hmm, this feeling.

06:43.778 --> 06:46.531
It's like he's hunting
for things that trigger me.

06:47.282 --> 06:49.659
[YUTA] Your pain was caused
thousands of years ago.

06:49.701 --> 06:52.329
The people alive today have
nothing to do with your regrets.

06:52.371 --> 06:55.665
How many have to die
until you finally feel avenged?

06:56.166 --> 06:57.376
Wait just a minute.

06:57.959 --> 07:00.045
Are you one of the Fujiwara?

07:00.419 --> 07:02.589
How can anyone
from your bloodline

07:02.630 --> 07:04.216
understand me?

07:06.343 --> 07:07.552
[Yuta grunts]

07:08.929 --> 07:10.805
[Takako grunting]

07:10.847 --> 07:12.349
[Takako growling]

07:14.517 --> 07:16.395
[RYU] Granite Blast.

07:25.612 --> 07:26.947
[YUTA] Ishigori?

07:27.197 --> 07:29.032
[TAKAKO]
It came from that rooftop.

07:29.074 --> 07:30.700
Too close for comfort.

07:31.201 --> 07:33.412
[YUTA] Even with Rika
protecting the stadium,

07:33.452 --> 07:36.039
a direct hit from an attack
on that level

07:36.081 --> 07:37.791
will leave several people dead.

07:37.832 --> 07:40.294
So I have to take
Ishigori out first.

07:40.335 --> 07:42.712
[TAKAKO] Now that Kurourushi
and Dhruv are gone,

07:42.754 --> 07:45.548
I have no reason
to let Ishigori run free.

07:45.590 --> 07:47.384
I'll take both him
and Okkotsu...

07:47.426 --> 07:48.676
- [YUTA] Now.
- [TAKAKO]...out.

07:50.262 --> 07:52.180
[RYU] Granite Blast!

08:05.026 --> 08:06.361
Come on.

08:06.403 --> 08:08.322
Don't disappoint me.

08:10.073 --> 08:11.283
He's gone?

08:11.325 --> 08:14.244
No. That's where Okkotsu
dug a hole earlier.

08:19.124 --> 08:20.125
Can't you fight

08:20.292 --> 08:21.709
without blowing up
everything around you?

08:22.002 --> 08:25.880
Oh, but that won't satisfy
my hunger, Okkotsu.

08:27.132 --> 08:28.842
JUJUTSU KAISEN

08:30.093 --> 08:33.430
Would you tell a starving kid
with a feast in front of him

08:33.472 --> 08:36.016
to take his time and eat slower?

08:37.434 --> 08:38.726
[YUTA] Wouldn't anyone?

08:40.145 --> 08:41.271
[RYU] I guess so.

08:41.313 --> 08:42.689
Most probably would.

08:42.730 --> 08:43.940
That was a bad example.

08:45.108 --> 08:49.196
My first run at life wasn't
completely lacking flavor.

08:49.237 --> 08:52.531
Some of the guys I fought
had real backbone.

08:52.573 --> 08:54.909
I even met a nice woman, too.

08:54.951 --> 08:58.497
Frankly, it'd be hard to say
I had any regrets at all.

09:00.874 --> 09:03.335
This vague hunger
I constantly feel

09:03.377 --> 09:06.213
is always gnawing
at me, Okkotsu.

09:06.254 --> 09:10.008
Everyone's always wondering
what I'm so unsatisfied about.

09:11.634 --> 09:15.305
These cigarettes have
a slightly sweet aftertaste.

09:17.015 --> 09:18.308
You know what it was?

09:18.766 --> 09:20.894
There was no dessert in my life.

09:21.978 --> 09:23.104
[YUTA] Here it comes.

09:23.146 --> 09:24.398
[thuds]

09:27.275 --> 09:28.276
[laughs]

09:28.318 --> 09:29.528
[punching]

09:31.363 --> 09:33.698
[RYU] Why am I unsatisfied?

09:34.157 --> 09:36.076
I think you know!

09:39.787 --> 09:41.164
- [gasps]
- [chuckles]

09:42.916 --> 09:43.875
[groans]

09:43.917 --> 09:45.502
[RYU] I'm unsatisfied

09:45.544 --> 09:47.504
because I'm not fulfilled!

09:50.673 --> 09:51.758
[grunts]

09:52.092 --> 09:53.134
[Ryu grunts]

09:57.972 --> 09:58.973
[gasps]

10:01.059 --> 10:02.894
You'd better not be crushed.

10:04.729 --> 10:05.855
[grunts]

10:10.277 --> 10:11.445
[choking]

10:12.320 --> 10:13.947
[grunting]

10:15.365 --> 10:16.575
[grunts]

10:17.700 --> 10:18.743
[grunts]

10:19.744 --> 10:21.455
[RYU] Hey, watch the hair.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.085
[grunts]

10:38.430 --> 10:39.473
[YUTA] Nice.

10:45.228 --> 10:48.148
[Ryu grunts]
Not calling your shikigami?

10:49.690 --> 10:51.025
I can't right now.

10:51.568 --> 10:53.528
Not with you going wild.

10:53.570 --> 10:55.614
[RYU] Oh, that's a shame.

10:56.573 --> 10:57.656
[running]

10:58.783 --> 11:00.910
[YUTA] He's probably
trying to limit where I can go.

11:01.869 --> 11:03.163
But I'll break through...

11:04.581 --> 11:05.915
head - on!

11:07.125 --> 11:08.585
Sweet!

11:08.793 --> 11:10.170
That's it, Okkotsu!

11:10.545 --> 11:12.088
Keep on coming!

11:14.382 --> 11:16.801
[YUTA] His cursed energy,
so precise!

11:22.557 --> 11:24.392
- Here's your reward!
- [gasps]

11:28.396 --> 11:29.564
Uh-oh.

11:30.106 --> 11:32.233
I overheated my hair.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.234
[creaks]

11:33.276 --> 11:34.361
[crashes]

11:38.657 --> 11:39.782
[grunts]

11:40.741 --> 11:42.452
[RYU] You're good, Okkotsu.

11:42.869 --> 11:44.538
Could you be the one?

11:44.579 --> 11:46.247
Are you my dessert?

11:49.917 --> 11:50.960
[Yuta grunts]

11:53.171 --> 11:54.506
You're great!

11:54.548 --> 11:57.300
Best I've seen so far!

12:01.429 --> 12:03.264
[TAKAKO]
What I strike isn't the person,

12:03.764 --> 12:05.724
but the surface of the sky.

12:05.766 --> 12:06.809
[shatters]

12:07.477 --> 12:08.811
Thin Ice Breaker!

12:12.065 --> 12:14.693
Get lost, you pile of vomit!

12:17.529 --> 12:19.197
Shut your mouth,

12:19.239 --> 12:21.241
- dick cheese!
- [gasps]

12:23.117 --> 12:24.285
[chuckles]

12:26.538 --> 12:28.373
This guy's resilient.

12:28.415 --> 12:29.916
Glad you're alive.

12:29.957 --> 12:32.001
I wanted to torment you
some more.

12:32.669 --> 12:34.879
[groans] What a hit.

12:34.921 --> 12:36.464
That was the first time
I've been forced

12:36.506 --> 12:38.091
to eat my own technique.

12:38.757 --> 12:41.428
Reverse cursed technique
is a pain to deal with,

12:41.469 --> 12:44.055
but it burns cursed energy
like crazy.

12:46.015 --> 12:49.728
We're finally seeing the bottom
of your reserves, Okkotsu.

12:50.019 --> 12:52.606
No matter how high - end
the sweet shop is,

12:52.647 --> 12:55.358
seeing the displays empty
at closing time

12:55.400 --> 12:57.569
is always disappointing.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.446
Guess it wasn't you.

12:59.487 --> 13:01.780
[panting]

13:05.619 --> 13:07.078
[YUTA] I wanted
to gain more distance

13:07.120 --> 13:08.829
from everyone in the stadium,

13:08.871 --> 13:10.789
keep them out of harm's way.

13:10.831 --> 13:11.999
Oh, well.

13:16.421 --> 13:18.339
Come to me, Rika.

13:19.090 --> 13:20.675
Give me everything!

13:21.301 --> 13:22.427
[both gasp]

13:23.219 --> 13:25.888
[TAKAKO] His shikigami
completely manifested?

13:25.930 --> 13:27.181
[RYU] How does that work?

13:27.223 --> 13:29.934
And he's swelling
with cursed energy again!

13:30.769 --> 13:33.438
[RIKA]
Which would you like, Yuta?

13:34.272 --> 13:35.440
Thank you.

13:35.482 --> 13:36.691
I'll take that one.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.318
[chuckles]

13:38.693 --> 13:41.112
[NARRATOR] Rika is
the stockpile of cursed energy

13:41.154 --> 13:43.864
and the externalization
of Okkotsu's technique.

13:43.906 --> 13:47.034
It remained with him
after Rika Orimoto passed on.

13:47.368 --> 13:49.412
While connected to Rika
through the ring,

13:49.454 --> 13:50.913
he gains the following.

13:50.955 --> 13:52.624
Use of his cursed technique,

13:52.666 --> 13:54.709
the complete manifestation
of Rika,

13:54.751 --> 13:57.170
and the cursed energy
supplied by Rika.

13:57.920 --> 14:00.340
Yuta can remain
connected to Rika

14:00.381 --> 14:01.966
for five minutes.

14:04.218 --> 14:05.261
[YUTA] Okay.

14:05.804 --> 14:06.887
Let's go.

14:07.888 --> 14:09.848
[TAKAKO] Don't
underestimate me. [gasps]

14:12.811 --> 14:13.770
[Yuta hisses]

14:14.061 --> 14:15.396
[YUTA] Don't move.

14:15.814 --> 14:17.482
[TAKAKO] Snake eyes and fangs.

14:17.524 --> 14:19.066
I can't move.

14:20.735 --> 14:21.944
[punching]

14:21.986 --> 14:23.446
[Takako groaning]

14:23.904 --> 14:25.281
Oh, man.

14:25.323 --> 14:27.158
You are super sweet, huh?

14:27.534 --> 14:28.951
[Takako groaning]

14:29.786 --> 14:30.787
[YUTA] Rika.

14:30.829 --> 14:32.288
- [RIKA] Right!
- [RYU] Yeah!

14:33.540 --> 14:34.624
[RYU] Oh, no!

14:34.666 --> 14:35.709
[thuds]

14:36.751 --> 14:37.918
[strains]

14:40.338 --> 14:42.089
That was close! Huh?

14:42.716 --> 14:45.844
[grunts] You can't
get rid of me that easy!

14:45.884 --> 14:47.886
♪

15:02.527 --> 15:03.486
[Takako grunts]

15:03.528 --> 15:05.321
- [Ryu groans]
- [gasps]

15:10.993 --> 15:12.036
[Yuta groans]

15:12.704 --> 15:13.747
[Rika gasps]

15:14.080 --> 15:15.248
[hisses]

15:15.289 --> 15:16.499
[RIKA] You!

15:16.541 --> 15:18.877
You hurt Yuta!

15:20.044 --> 15:21.045
[Takako gasps]

15:21.087 --> 15:22.088
[grunts]

15:25.924 --> 15:26.967
[gasps]

15:27.802 --> 15:29.429
[whooshing]

15:29.470 --> 15:30.971
[YUTA] What now?

15:31.681 --> 15:32.931
[RYU] Let's go!

15:32.973 --> 15:34.141
[Yuta grunts]

15:35.268 --> 15:36.269
[laughs]

15:36.603 --> 15:38.897
[YUTA] Even with this,
I can't fully block it.

15:42.483 --> 15:44.402
- Wanna go?
- [grunts]

15:49.616 --> 15:50.658
[Rika grunts]

16:01.377 --> 16:02.420
[gasps]

16:06.466 --> 16:07.884
[Takako grunts]

16:08.092 --> 16:09.302
[growls]

16:09.343 --> 16:10.344
[cracks]

16:10.386 --> 16:11.429
[gasps]

16:12.764 --> 16:14.849
[TAKAKO] Thin Ice Breaker!

16:23.524 --> 16:24.692
[scoffs]

16:25.109 --> 16:26.193
The Sun, Moon, and Stars Squad
was Fujiwara Clan's assassins.

16:26.611 --> 16:27.403
We lived in darkness and served
with selfless devotion.

16:27.946 --> 16:28.822
We were even forbidden
from having our own names.

16:29.071 --> 16:29.864
Yet that man
once granted me a name.

16:29.988 --> 16:30.865
So he could execute me instead

16:31.115 --> 16:31.825
for his crime
of slaying his own kin.

16:32.116 --> 16:34.993
[scoffs] Fujiwara!

16:35.328 --> 16:38.038
[RYU] I've still got
a strong appetite!

16:38.414 --> 16:40.291
[growls]

16:40.333 --> 16:42.460
Let's keep chowing down!

16:44.128 --> 16:46.422
[TAKAKO]
It's always you, Fujiwara!

16:46.464 --> 16:48.424
You're always getting in my way!

16:48.800 --> 16:50.510
Are you that afraid of me?

16:50.551 --> 16:53.220
Afraid of me
becoming my own person?

16:53.262 --> 16:54.848
- [hisses]
- [grunts]

16:58.852 --> 17:01.729
[NARRATOR] Okkotsu
defeated Dhruv Lakdawalla,

17:02.396 --> 17:05.316
whose technique made
the path of his shikigami

17:05.358 --> 17:06.567
into his domain,

17:06.609 --> 17:10.237
which cut into anything
it touched.

17:10.530 --> 17:11.489
[slashes]

17:11.531 --> 17:12.824
[gasps]

17:13.533 --> 17:15.952
[TAKAKO]
This is Dhruv's technique.

17:17.035 --> 17:18.120
Does that mean

17:18.162 --> 17:21.374
Okkotsu's technique is Copy?

17:22.333 --> 17:24.126
[Yuta grunting]

17:24.168 --> 17:25.545
[Takako grunting]

17:27.296 --> 17:29.131
[Ryu grunting]

17:30.550 --> 17:31.676
[punching]

17:34.094 --> 17:36.556
[YUTA] I don't know
what my ancestors did to you,

17:36.597 --> 17:38.766
but that has nothing
to do with me.

17:38.808 --> 17:40.643
If you live only
for your own sake,

17:40.685 --> 17:42.645
you're eventually
going to reach your limit.

17:42.687 --> 17:43.813
[TAKAKO] Shut up!

17:43.855 --> 17:45.940
Live for the sake of others?

17:45.982 --> 17:48.234
You think I'll eventually
reach my limit?

17:49.694 --> 17:52.070
Stop barking those things at me!

17:52.112 --> 17:54.782
It's easy for you to say.
You've already become someone!

17:54.824 --> 17:55.909
[snickers]

17:59.620 --> 18:00.788
[grunts]

18:01.873 --> 18:03.499
[♪ tense music playing]

18:10.297 --> 18:11.799
[RYU] Quit your whining!

18:12.174 --> 18:14.010
Because at this point,

18:15.177 --> 18:18.056
words are meaningless!

18:22.643 --> 18:24.478
[ALL] Domain Expansion!

18:26.856 --> 18:29.316
Yuta! Give him back!

18:29.859 --> 18:32.653
[TAKAKO] Even if it tries
to penetrate the barrier later.

18:32.695 --> 18:34.321
[RYU]
I ain't gonna drag this out!

18:34.363 --> 18:36.699
Let's settle this,
nice and sweet!

18:39.077 --> 18:40.411
[NARRATOR] At that moment,

18:40.453 --> 18:43.039
the black devil
of the modern age...

18:43.081 --> 18:44.999
[KUROURUSHI] I told you,

18:45.041 --> 18:47.752
I like the taste of iron!

18:48.126 --> 18:50.212
[NARRATOR]
...flew into the barriers.

18:51.213 --> 18:52.298
[all gasp]

18:52.632 --> 18:55.593
[NARRATOR] Kurourushi
had completed parthenogenesis

18:55.635 --> 18:57.261
before going dormant.

18:58.638 --> 19:01.265
So Kurourushi
was still alive and well

19:01.307 --> 19:02.600
as a cursed spirit.

19:03.017 --> 19:04.978
The complex forces
of their domains

19:05.019 --> 19:07.814
had been keeping
the three sorcerers in check.

19:07.855 --> 19:09.440
But this intruder

19:09.482 --> 19:11.025
was unexpected.

19:11.525 --> 19:13.569
And so the barriers...

19:16.196 --> 19:17.615
collapsed.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.831
[TAKAKO]
How's Kurourushi still alive?

19:24.872 --> 19:26.082
- [Yuta grunts]
- [Takako gasps]

19:28.375 --> 19:30.086
- [grunts]
- [shatters]

19:30.128 --> 19:32.005
[TAKAKO] Damn!
I can't use my technique

19:32.046 --> 19:33.881
right after Domain Expansion.

19:33.923 --> 19:35.341
- [Kurourushi growls]
- [Takako gasps]

19:36.843 --> 19:40.763
[Rika chomping]

19:40.805 --> 19:42.723
How dare you take my arm!

19:42.765 --> 19:45.518
- Fujiwara!
- [RYU] Enough, Uro.

19:45.559 --> 19:46.644
Quiet.

19:47.603 --> 19:50.773
You and the roach were
never invited to my table.

19:52.358 --> 19:54.027
Granite Blast.

19:54.068 --> 19:55.361
[explosion]

19:57.446 --> 20:01.034
[NARRATOR] Ishigori's technique
is Cursed Energy Discharge.

20:01.075 --> 20:03.410
It's an extremely simple attack,

20:03.452 --> 20:05.538
but it performs just as well,

20:05.579 --> 20:08.916
even when his technique
is burnt out.

20:09.876 --> 20:11.293
[Kurourushi growling]

20:17.050 --> 20:18.092
Now.

20:21.303 --> 20:23.389
Welcome to my table...

20:24.765 --> 20:25.892
Okkotsu.

20:27.018 --> 20:29.103
- Rika, let's go.
- [growls]

20:33.566 --> 20:37.277
[NARRATOR] Okkotsu can discharge
a high volume of cursed energy,

20:37.319 --> 20:40.406
but only while Rika
is completely manifested.

20:40.447 --> 20:44.202
However, his maximum output
is slightly inferior

20:44.242 --> 20:45.536
to Ishigori's.

20:45.703 --> 20:48.748
So he planned to charge
and unleash his cursed energy

20:48.789 --> 20:51.792
before Ishigori
reached maximum output.

20:51.834 --> 20:54.378
- [Yuta gasps]
- But he changed his mind.

20:55.088 --> 20:57.757
LET'S LET IT ALL OUT!

20:57.798 --> 21:00.300
400 years of longing.

21:00.760 --> 21:03.721
The intense gaze
full of that hunger

21:03.763 --> 21:06.306
melted Yuta Okkotsu's heart,

21:06.682 --> 21:09.810
even though he would
likely never find meaning

21:09.852 --> 21:11.269
in fighting.

21:12.855 --> 21:14.648
All right, just this once.

21:16.525 --> 21:18.444
♪

21:22.073 --> 21:23.032
[both grunt]

21:23.074 --> 21:24.867
[♪ theme song playing]

21:33.417 --> 21:36.963
That was some
seriously sweet stuff, Okkotsu!

21:39.006 --> 21:40.091
[Yuta grunts]

21:47.181 --> 21:48.724
Yeah, attaboy!

21:48.766 --> 21:51.227
Let's keep
this dinner party going!

21:54.563 --> 21:56.857
That big thing
can fire on its own?

21:57.650 --> 21:58.734
But...

21:59.610 --> 22:01.403
its force is weak!

22:02.947 --> 22:05.825
After Domain Expansion
and a meal with me,

22:06.159 --> 22:08.368
even you haven't had
enough time to digest

22:08.410 --> 22:10.370
and recover your full strength.

22:11.664 --> 22:13.249
I'll end this!

22:13.331 --> 22:15.960
Granite Blast!

22:17.711 --> 22:20.214
♪

22:20.256 --> 22:22.091
[NARRATOR]
But Okkotsu's technique...

22:23.759 --> 22:25.761
had already recovered.

22:26.720 --> 22:27.721
[Ryu gasps]

22:28.514 --> 22:30.390
[RYU]
He's using Uro's technique!

22:31.184 --> 22:33.936
I knew he was more than just
a cursed speech user.

22:34.312 --> 22:35.729
And I figured that big thing

22:35.771 --> 22:37.023
probably had
a different technique

22:37.064 --> 22:38.274
from Okkotsu's, too.

22:38.607 --> 22:39.942
So that's it!

22:39.984 --> 22:41.902
Okkotsu's technique is Copy!

22:42.195 --> 22:44.404
But there should be
strenuous conditions on it.

22:44.446 --> 22:46.282
When did he satisfy
those conditions?

22:46.324 --> 22:47.283
While I wasn't looking?

22:47.325 --> 22:48.909
Maybe there aren't any!

22:49.618 --> 22:50.786
[Yuta grunts]

22:53.664 --> 22:55.082
[RYU] That was when he did it!

22:55.624 --> 22:56.876
[YUTA] Thin Ice Breaker!

22:58.919 --> 22:59.837
[Ryu groans]

22:59.879 --> 23:01.505
- [Rika growls]
- [Yuta grunts]

23:06.468 --> 23:07.803
[beeps]

23:08.386 --> 23:09.429
[NARRATOR] Five minutes.

23:09.930 --> 23:13.351
Okkotsu's connection
to Rika was severed.

23:13.767 --> 23:15.561
- [growls]
- [Yuta gasps]

23:19.523 --> 23:20.983
[RIKA] Yuta!

23:22.860 --> 23:23.903
[Yuta grunts]

23:24.820 --> 23:26.530
[RYU] Is this the feeling?

23:26.572 --> 23:27.698
[Yuta groans]

23:28.824 --> 23:29.909
[grunts]

23:30.243 --> 23:33.329
[RYU] There's still more
after going all out!

23:33.371 --> 23:35.956
♪

23:36.498 --> 23:37.917
This is what it's like

23:38.292 --> 23:40.044
to eat dessert!

23:55.351 --> 23:56.810
[chuckles, grunts]

24:00.814 --> 24:01.857
[grunts]

24:02.149 --> 24:03.401
[YUTA] We're done.

24:07.071 --> 24:08.197
[RYU] What?

24:08.655 --> 24:09.949
What does he mean?

24:10.324 --> 24:11.200
[gasps]

24:11.242 --> 24:13.827
♪

24:23.545 --> 24:26.006
[panting]

24:27.091 --> 24:29.760
Was that my technique?

24:32.305 --> 24:33.597
I see.

24:33.639 --> 24:35.682
He sent it sailing back to me

24:35.724 --> 24:37.684
using Uro's technique.

24:41.105 --> 24:42.773
Thank you, Okkotsu.

24:43.149 --> 24:44.233
[cutlery clinks]

24:49.405 --> 24:51.365
I'm full now.

24:51.407 --> 24:52.490
[chuckles]

24:54.743 --> 24:55.995
[thuds]

25:02.376 --> 25:03.501
[gasps]

25:06.797 --> 25:07.840
[sighs]

25:09.300 --> 25:12.094
Okkotsu, you're too soft.

25:12.136 --> 25:13.804
That's not a compliment.

25:13.846 --> 25:16.598
Sparing the life of a sorcerer
who fought to kill you--

25:16.640 --> 25:18.851
[YUTA] There's nothing
to gain from killing you.

25:18.892 --> 25:20.560
Uro told me the same thing.

25:21.228 --> 25:23.730
[RYU] You mean
that woman's still alive?

25:24.815 --> 25:27.276
Well, I guess
my blast was weaker

25:27.318 --> 25:29.362
after my Domain Expansion.

25:29.403 --> 25:32.156
Hey, what was it
she kept going on about?

25:32.656 --> 25:34.158
Were you having a lovers' spat?

25:34.200 --> 25:36.035
Yeah, something like that.

25:36.452 --> 25:38.204
Eh, don't let her get to ya.

25:38.245 --> 25:40.164
[YUTA] There's nothing
I can say to that woman

25:40.206 --> 25:41.499
to change her mind.

25:42.041 --> 25:44.751
Anything I do say
will lead to violence.

25:45.378 --> 25:48.339
You see,
it's because I'm blessed.

25:48.381 --> 25:50.257
[Ryu sighs]
Is that how it works?

25:50.299 --> 25:52.009
Because frankly, I don't get it.

25:52.468 --> 25:55.179
[Yuta sighs] Well, regardless,

25:55.888 --> 25:57.139
can I have your points?

25:57.181 --> 25:58.224
Huh?

25:59.933 --> 26:01.394
Now I get it.

26:01.435 --> 26:03.354
So if we didn't
give you our points,

26:03.396 --> 26:04.897
you would have killed us, right?

26:05.563 --> 26:08.859
[Yuta grunts]
I'm not so sure about that.

26:11.153 --> 26:12.405
[chuckles] All I know is

26:12.446 --> 26:14.532
you should be grateful
to my friends.

26:17.451 --> 26:20.746
THROUGH THE TRANSFER
OF RYU AND TAKAKO'S POINTS,

26:20.954 --> 26:23.581
YUTA OKKOTSU
CAME TO POSSESS 190 POINTS.

26:24.833 --> 26:26.335
[♪ melancholic music playing]

26:26.377 --> 26:29.046
[TAKAKO] You're the one
who's going to reach your limit.

26:32.799 --> 26:34.134
I've seen it.

26:38.305 --> 26:41.100
Be it sorcerer or cursed spirit,

26:41.350 --> 26:45.062
all are driven over the edge
by the same thing.

26:45.104 --> 26:46.688
Overwhelming aggression

26:46.730 --> 26:49.900
that blinds them
to everything else.

26:49.942 --> 26:51.693
Like a calamity.

26:56.740 --> 26:59.785
TO BE CONTINUED

27:00.244 --> 27:02.413
[♪ closing theme song playing]
